SIMPLE: wayward
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wayward
<hw>Way"ward</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>weiward</ets>, for <ets>aweiward</ets>, i. e., turned away. See
<er>Away</er>, and <er>-ward</er>.]</ety> <def>Taking one's own way;
disobedient; froward; perverse; willful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My wife is in a <qex>wayward</qex> mood.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Wayward</qex> beauty doth not fancy move.</q>
<rj><qau>Fairfax.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wilt thou forgive the <qex>wayward</qex> thought?</q>
<rj><qau>Keble.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Way"ward*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Way"ward*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Way-wise</ent>⟦br⟧
